<%= HEADERS %> | <%= HEADER_AUTH %><br/><%= HEADER_CT_JSON %>
<%= REQUEST %> | [Attachment object](#attachment-object) limited to the following attributes:<ul><li>**attachmentSubType**</li><li>**attachmentType**</li><li>**description** (applicable when attaching to sheet or row only)</li><li>**name**</li><li>**url**</li></ul>
<%= RETURNS %> | [Result object](#result-object) containing an [Attachment object](#attachment-object) for the newly created attachment
<%= SCOPE %> | WRITE_SHEETS

The URL can be any of the following:
<ul>
<li>Normal URL (attachmentType "LINK")</li>
<li>Box.com URL (attachmentType "BOX_COM")</li>
<li>Dropbox URL (attachmentType "DROPBOX")</li>
<li>Egnyte URL (attachmentType "EGNYTE")</li>
<li>Evernote URL (attachmentType "EVERNOTE")</li>
<li>Google Drive URL (attachmentType "GOOGLE_DRIVE")</li>
<li>OneDrive URL (attachmentType "ONEDRIVE")</li>
</ul>

<aside class="notice">For <b>GOOGLE_DRIVE</b> attachments that are Google Docs, the <b>attachmentSubType</b> attribute can be optionally included to indicate the type of a file.  Valid values are: <b>DOCUMENT</b>, <b>DRAWING</b>, <b>PDF</b>, <b>PRESENTATION</b>, <b>SPREADSHEET</b></aside>

<aside class="notice">For EGNYTE attachments which are folders, the <b>attachmentSubType</b> attribute must be included with a value of <b>FOLDER</b>.</aside>

<aside class="notice">When the attachment type is <b>BOX_COM</b>, <b>DROPBOX</b>, <b>EGNYTE</b> (without an <b>attachmentSubType</b> specified), <b>GOOGLE_DRIVE</b> (without an <b>attachmentSubType</b> specified), or <b>ONEDRIVE</b>, the <b>mimeType</b> is derived by the file extension specified on the <b>name</b> attribute.</aside>

<aside class="notice">Smartsheetgov.com accounts are restricted to the following attachment types: BOX_COM, FILE, GOOGLE_DRIVE, LINK, or ONEDRIVE.</aside>
